excerpt: Home of the inspiration for "Dolphin Tale," this aquarium exhibits marine mammals & sea turtles.
detail_description: Located in Clearwater Beach, the Clearwater Marine Aquarium is a renowned facility dedicated to rescuing, rehabilitating, and releasing marine animals. It was established in 1972 and is housed in a former water treatment plant with large pools ideal for rehabilitation operations. The aquarium is home to various injured marine life that cannot return to the wild. One of its most famous residents was Winter, a bottle-nosed dolphin whose story inspired the movie 'Dolphin Tale.'
name: Clearwater Marine Aquarium

excerpt: Laid-back Clearwater Beach is known for its namesake stretch of soft, white sand, which draws visitors year-round for jet-skiing, parasailing, and stand-up paddleboarding in its calm waters. Cyclists and rollerbladers glide along a winding beachfront promenade lined with casual seafood restaurants and cafes. Come sunset, Pier 60 hosts a nightly festival with street performers and craft vendors.
detail_description: Clearwater Beach is a laid-back destination famous for its soft, white sand and calm waters, perfect for activities like jet-skiing, parasailing, and paddleboarding. The beachfront promenade offers a scenic route for cyclists and rollerbladers with plenty of seafood restaurants and cafes to explore. As the sun sets, Pier 60 comes alive with nightly festivals featuring street performers and craft vendors.
name: Clearwater Beach

excerpt: Long fishing pier offering pavilions, telescopes & a bait house with snacks, plus sunset views.
detail_description: Pier 60 is a popular fishing pier in Clearwater, offering pavilions, telescopes, and a bait house with snacks. Visitors can enjoy nightly sunset celebrations two hours before and after sunset, featuring local vendors, artists, and musicians. For just $1, you can explore the remaining 1,080 feet of the pier for recreational fishing with beautiful beach views.
name: Pier 60

excerpt: Expansive white-sand beach offering plenty of room for picnics, surfing & other outdoor activities.
detail_description: Sand Key Park is a stunning waterfront destination in Clearwater, offering a long stretch of pristine white sand and clear water. It combines the beauty of the beach with park amenities such as a dog park, cabanas, and a playground. Despite its scenic beauty, it's less crowded than Clearwater Beach. Visitors can enjoy picnics, surfing, and other outdoor activities while taking in the local marine wildlife. The park also features a salt marsh area with benches for bird-watching and relaxation.
name: Sand Key Park

excerpt: Tranquil, oak-lined paths, educational walking tours, natural exhibits & educational kids' camps.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Clearwater, Moccasin Lake Nature Park is a serene escape that offers an enchanting blend of nature and education. Spanning over 50 acres, this hidden gem features tranquil oak-lined paths and diverse wildlife, including birds of prey and peacocks. Visitors can explore 1.5 miles of boardwalk trails that meander through lush forests, making it perfect for leisurely strolls or more challenging hikes with stunning views from elevated bluffs.
name: Moccasin Lake Nature Park
address: 2750 Park Trail Ln, Clearwater, FL 33759, USA

excerpt: Island park with white sand beaches plus swimming, boating, fishing & picnic facilities.
detail_description: Caladesi Island State Park is a serene oasis just off Clearwater's coast, offering visitors an escape from the usual tourist hustle. This pristine island can only be reached by ferry or kayak, making it a hidden gem for those seeking tranquility. With its stunning white sand beaches, it's ideal for beachcombing and shelling enthusiasts eager to discover unique seashells along the shore.
name: Caladesi Island State Park

excerpt: Known for the variety of shells on its shores, this park also offers swimming, fishing & hiking.
detail_description: Honeymoon Island State Park, located in Dunedin, is a barrier island known for its pristine four-mile white-sand beach and clear, calm waters. Visitors can enjoy swimming, fishing, and hiking while taking in the natural beauty of the virgin slash pine forest. The park offers amenities such as showers, restrooms, a cafe serving food and drinks, and rentals for bicycles, kayaks, beach chairs, and umbrellas.
name: Honeymoon Island State Park

excerpt: Roomy, modern setting for a slate of music, comedy & Broadway shows, plus arts education.
detail_description: Ruth Eckerd Hall, located in Clearwater, is a spacious and contemporary concert venue that offers a diverse range of entertainment including music, comedy, and Broadway shows. The hall's design ensures an unobstructed view from every seat, providing an intimate and immersive experience for all guests. Known for hosting renowned musicians and electrifying concerts, it has become a go-to destination for live performances in the Tampa Bay area.
name: Ruth Eckerd Hall
address: 1111 McMullen Booth Rd, Clearwater, FL 33759, USA

detail_description: Embark on an exciting adventure with Captain Memo’s Pirate Cruise, a thrilling experience for all ages. Step aboard the authentic pirate ship replica and set sail across Clearwater Bay and the Gulf of Mexico. The spirited crew leads passengers in treasure hunts, limbo dances, and games with water guns and hula hoops. With guaranteed dolphin sightings and possible glimpses of sharks, rays, and manatees, this two-hour sightseeing cruise offers fun activities for both adults and children since 1993.
name: Captain Memo’s Pirate Cruise
address: 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: Nestled right across from Clearwater Beach Municipal Marina, this vibrant locale is a hub for all things boating and water-related. Just a stone's throw away from the lively Pier 60, famous for its enchanting sunset celebrations, visitors can indulge in an array of activities. The marina boasts stunning views and calm waters, making it an ideal spot for families with young children to explore. From fishing trips to dolphin tours and parasailing adventures, there's no shortage of excitement here!
name: Clearwater Beach Municipal Marina

detail_description: The Clearwater Ferry offers a convenient and enjoyable way to travel from Dunedin Marina to Clearwater Beach. Passengers can enjoy the scenic ride and may even spot dolphins along the way. The ferry also makes stops at locations like Coachman Park before heading straight to the beach. Travelers recommend bringing a towel for windy conditions, but overall find the experience affordable and free of holiday traffic and parking hassles. They also emphasize the importance of tipping the captain for their service.
name: Clearwater Ferry

detail_description: Spectrum Field is a small, intimate baseball stadium in Clearwater, Florida that is home to the local minor league team, the Clearwater Threshers. The stadium has an electrifying atmosphere and is particularly popular with Phillies fans during spring training sessions. Tickets for minor league baseball games tend to be cheaper than tickets for televised MLB matches.
name: BayCare Ballpark
address: 601 N, Old Coachman Rd., Clearwater, FL 33765, USA

detail_description: Countryside Mall, located in Clearwater, FL, is a popular destination for shopping and dining. Since its opening in 1975, the mall has expanded to feature over 150 boutiques and flagship stores spread across two floors. Fashion enthusiasts can explore a variety of trendy stores such as American Eagle Outfitters, Hollister, Forever 21, and Victorias Secret.
name: Countryside Mall
address: 27001 US Hwy 19 N Suite 1039, Clearwater, FL 33761, USA

excerpt: Creekside green space with a boat launch & fishing area, plus disc golf, trails & picnic spots.
detail_description: This park is a great place to spend a day outdoors. There are a variety of activities available, including fishing, hiking, and cycling. The park is also home to a disc golf course.
name: Cliff Stephens Park

excerpt: Linear 38.2-mile recreation rail trail from St. Petersburg to Tarpon Springs for cycling & walking.
detail_description: The Fred Marquis Pinellas Trail is a 38.2-mile recreational rail trail that spans from St. Petersburg to Tarpon Springs, offering a picturesque journey along Florida's western shore. This linear trail provides stunning Gulf Coast views and takes travelers through urban waterfronts and charming downtown areas. Additionally, it connects to other trail systems, including a 75-mile loop within Pinellas County and the Coast-to-Coast Connector Trail, which stretches 250 miles across the state.
name: Fred Marquis Pinellas Trail

excerpt: This serene state park with a sandy beach, nature trails & bayside mangrove forest draws kayakers.
detail_description: Caladesi Island is a serene state park with sandy beaches, nature trails, and a bayside mangrove forest that attracts kayakers. The Rotary Centennial Nature Center offers educational services on the park's history and natural resources. Accessible only by ferry from Honeymoon Island, this pristine island is a nature lover's paradise.
name: Caladesi Island

excerpt: Shorefront spot with paved walkways hosting a variety of concerts, festivals & exhibitions all year.
detail_description: Coachman Park is a picturesque shorefront destination with paved walkways that hosts a variety of events throughout the year, including concerts, festivals, and exhibitions. Situated in Clearwater, Florida, this park offers stunning views of the waterfront and is home to the Baycare Sound venue. With covered seating for 4,000 guests and space for lawn seating, it has attracted renowned performers such as Ringo Starr, Kenny Loggins, Melissa Etheridge, and more.
name: Coachman Park

detail_description: Embark on a delightful experience aboard the Calypso Queen, where you can dance, dine, and enjoy scenic views. The Tropical Twilight Cruise offers an all-you-can-eat and drink experience with a live DJ as you cruise along Clearwater Harbor. Keep an eye out for dolphins, pelicans, and maybe even a manatee. For those seeking a combination of great food and sightseeing, the Tropical Buffet Lunch Sightseeing Cruise is perfect.
name: Calypso Queen
address: Slip #56, 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: Clearwater Tiki Boat Tours offer a fun and lively experience on the water. The cruise takes you around the Gulf of Mexico, providing stunning views of Clearwater Beach. Guests can bring their own snacks and drinks to enjoy while taking in the sights from the floating bar. The boat tour is known for its knowledgeable and personable crew who create a welcoming atmosphere for all guests.
name: Clearwater Tiki Boat Tours
address: 25 Causeway Blvd SLIP #5, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Art deco-style venue hosting a mix of events, from comedy acts to musicals, plus film screenings.
detail_description: The Nancy and David Bilheimer Capitol Theatre, situated in downtown Clearwater, Florida, is a renowned cultural landmark with a rich history dating back to 1921. This vintage Art Deco-style venue hosts an array of events including comedy acts, musicals, film screenings, and big-name touring performances in an intimate setting for up to 750 people. The theater's elegant architecture has been meticulously preserved through extensive renovations while integrating modern facilities.
name: Nancy and David Bilheimer Capitol Theatre

excerpt: Polished hotel with 10 acres of private beach, plus 2 outdoor pools, multiple eateries & kids' club.
detail_description: Nestled on a 10-acre private beach, Hilton Clearwater Beach Resort & Spa offers a luxurious experience with elegant rooms, top-notch amenities, and exquisite dining options. The hotel features two outdoor pools, a modern gym, diverse restaurants serving global cuisine, a Starbucks outlet, and a beach tiki bar for enjoying tropical cocktails at sunset.
name: Hilton Clearwater Beach Resort & Spa

detail_description: Little Toot Dolphin Adventure is a family-friendly option for those looking to get out on the water and see dolphins up close. The tours depart from the municipal marina and offer day tours as well as sunset tours. On board, guests can purchase drinks while the captain provides information about the local wildlife. The experience guarantees sightings of dolphins and may also include glimpses of sharks, rays, and manatees.
name: Little Toot Dolphin Adventure
address: 25 Causeway Blvd Slip 48, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Laid-back beachfront hangout dishes seafood & drinks amid picnic tables, a deck & gulf views.
detail_description: Palm Pavilion Beachside Grill & Bar is a laid-back beachfront hangout known for its seafood and drinks with a Tommy Bahama feel. The menu offers a variety of appetizers, bowls, salads, sandwiches, burgers, wraps, and entrees like coconut shrimp and St. Louis-style barbecue ribs. It's also famous for being one of the best spots to watch sunsets while enjoying tropical beverages and live music.
name: Palm Pavilion Beachside Grill & Bar

excerpt: Adventure-themed mini-golf course with waterfalls, gator feedings, scavenger hunts & arcade games.
detail_description: Located in Clearwater, FL, Congo River Golf is an adventure-themed mini golf course with waterfalls, gator feedings and scavenger hunts. The mini golf course is relatively difficult and has a cool Adventure theme.
name: Congo River Golf
address: 20060 US Hwy 19 N, Clearwater, FL 33764, USA

excerpt: Clearwater is a city and the county seat of Pinellas County, Florida, United States, west of Tampa and north of St. Petersburg. To the west of Clearwater lies the Gulf of Mexico and to the southeast lies Tampa Bay. As of the 2020 census, the city had a population of 117,292. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Clearwater, located in Florida's Tampa Bay area, is famous for its sunny weather and stunning gulf coast beaches. Clearwater Beach, stretching 3 miles on a barrier island, offers pristine white sand and is lined with hotels and dining options. The city is also home to the Clearwater Marine Aquarium where injured dolphins and sea turtles are rehabilitated. Additionally, visitors can catch spring training games of the Phillies pro baseball team at Spectrum Field.
name: Clearwater

excerpt: Dunedin is a city on Florida’s Gulf Coast. It’s known for the beaches, pine forest and ospreys of Honeymoon Island State Park. The island is linked to the mainland by Dunedin Causeway, which offers views over St. Joseph Sound. Downtown, Hammock Park is home to owls, woodpeckers and a butterfly garden. The Fred Marquis Pinellas Trail runs through the city. West, kayaks dot the mangroves of Caladesi Island State Park.
detail_description: Dunedin, located on Florida's Gulf Coast, is a charming city known for its natural beauty and outdoor attractions. Honeymoon Island State Park offers pristine beaches, pine forests, and the opportunity to spot ospreys, while the Dunedin Causeway provides stunning views of St. Joseph Sound. In the downtown area, Hammock Park is a haven for wildlife enthusiasts with its resident owls, woodpeckers, and butterfly garden.
name: Dunedin

excerpt: Grouper sandwiches are the specialty at this longtime seafood shack with colorful, festive decor.
detail_description: Frenchy's Rockaway Grill is a renowned seafood shack located in Clearwater Beach, known for its vibrant and festive atmosphere. This beachfront bar offers a unique experience with live rock and roll bands playing hits from the 70s and 80s. The menu features Floribbean-style dishes, including the famous grouper sandwich available in various styles such as Cajun, Caribbean, and Reuben.
name: Frenchy's Rockaway Grill

detail_description: The Tropics Boat Tours at Clearwater Beach offers an exciting and educational experience for families. Their tropical-themed double-decker catamarans can accommodate up to 125 guests, providing excellent viewing opportunities for spotting dolphins, manatees, and sea turtles. The tours guarantee dolphin sightings and offer a fun-filled adventure with onboard guides pointing out these playful creatures. With various boat tours available, including the Dolphin Exploration Tour, visitors are promised an unforgettable experience exploring the beauty of the area.
name: The Tropics Boat Tours
address: 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Upscale rooms, some with ocean views, plus a private beach, modern dining & an outdoor pool.
detail_description: The Sheraton Sand Key Resort offers upscale rooms, some with ocean views, and a private beach. Guests can enjoy modern dining options and an outdoor pool. Rustys Bistro at the resort is known for its Thanksgiving buffet featuring a variety of delectable dishes including Gulf favorites like cocktail shrimp, oysters, and crab claws. The carving station offers citrus-marinated turkey and other savory options. Additionally, there's a chef's fall dessert table with cakes, pies, cookies, and more.
name: Clearwater Beach Sheraton Resort on Sand Key
address: 1160 Gulf Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: Jolley Trolley Transportation offers a convenient and scenic way to explore Clearwater Beach and the surrounding towns. The trolley operates along the coastal route, providing easy access to various attractions. Additionally, it is available for charter services for special events. Customers have praised the company for its excellent service during weddings and other occasions. With affordable fares for seniors and adults, Jolley Trolley provides a cost-effective transportation option compared to rideshare services like Uber or Lyft.
name: Jolley Trolley Transportation
address: 1230 S Myrtle Ave Suite 301, Clearwater, FL 33756, USA

detail_description: The Ream Wilson Clearwater Trail, also known as the Clearwater East West Trail, is a long pathway that currently connects four parks and will eventually stretch from Tampa to the Gulf of Mexico in Florida. It is popular for biking and walking, with amenities such as new bathrooms, parking lots, playgrounds, tennis courts, and basketball courts along the way. The trail offers a separated path for various activities like walking, running, and rolling.
name: Ream Wilson Trail

excerpt: Amusement park with bumper boats, arcade, mini-golf, go-karts & more as well as American eats.
detail_description: Celebration Station is an amusement park located not far from Downtown Celebration. It offers a variety of thrilling rides and activities for kids, including bumper boats, mini-golf, go-karts, arcade games, and more. The park also features an on-site restaurant serving American eats. With its arcade boasting over 100 games, batting cages, pool tables, and amusement rides for younger children, Celebration Station provides a fun-filled day out for families and friends.
name: Celebration Station
address: 24546 US Hwy 19 N, Clearwater, FL 33763, USA

excerpt: Stylish shopping center featuring boutiques for clothes & beachwear, plus bars & casual restaurants.
detail_description: Pelican Walk Plaza Clearwater Beach Florida is a mall with boutiques, restaurants, and bars. It's perfect for shoppers looking for something to do in Clearwater while they're on vacation.
name: Pelican Walk Plaza Clearwater Beach Florida

detail_description: Flowrider Indoor Surfing at Clearwater Beach offers an exhilarating and secure indoor surfing experience for surfers of all levels. Whether you're a seasoned pro or a beginner, this wave house brand provides the perfect setting to catch some waves. The modern technology creates an artificial wave that mimics real-time surfing conditions, making it a great place to learn and practice without worrying about wipeouts.
name: Flowrider Indoor Surfing
address: 311 S Gulfview Blvd, Clearwater, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: StarLite Cruises is a well-established family-owned business in Clearwater Beach, offering a diverse range of vessels to cater to different group sizes. With over 3 million satisfied customers since its inception in 1986, it has become one of the most trusted cruise operators in the region. The StarLite Majesty provides an elegant and exciting experience with its twin-decked entertainment venue, allowing guests to enjoy stunning coastal views while dining and dancing.
name: StarLite Cruises

excerpt: Wide, sandy beach featuring water sports, rental umbrellas, dolphins & beachfront restaurants.
detail_description: Clearwater Beach in Florida is a perfect destination for families, offering a wide sandy beach with water sports, rental umbrellas, and the chance to spot dolphins. The area provides activities for everyone, from building sandcastles with the kids to snorkeling or diving. Visitors can also enjoy go-karts and other attractions within walking distance of various vacation rentals. For a unique experience, travelers can take an illuminated kayak tour in nearby Treasure Island with Glass Bottom Tours.
name: Clearwater Beach

detail_description: A Boat Day is a top-rated boat tour experience in Florida, offering tailored tours in Clearwater, Dunedin, and Indian Rocks Beach. With various boats to choose from, they cater to all ages and preferences. Clearwater Beach is a haven for water enthusiasts with its beautiful beaches and exciting water sports. A Boat Day offers an amazing experience with friendly staff and knowledgeable captains who showcase the area's highlights, including playful dolphins and unique marine life.
name: A Boat Day

detail_description: Clearwater Island Boat Tours offers private boat tours where visitors can cruise the Gulf of Mexico on a double-decker boat, spotting wildlife like manatees, stingrays, and dolphins. The tour includes visits to the best area beaches for shelling, swimming, and snorkeling. Guests have praised Captain Matt for his friendly and personable nature, as well as his provision of cold water, ice chest with plenty of ice for drinks and snorkel gear.
name: Clearwater Island Boat Tours

detail_description: Beach Walk is a popular destination known for its iconic Pier 60, offering breathtaking sunset views and a variety of entertainment options. Situated along Causeway Boulevard near the Clearwater Marine Aquarium, this pier provides an ideal vantage point overlooking the Gulf of Mexico, making it a must-visit spot for visitors seeking picturesque experiences by the sea.
name: Beach walk

excerpt: Picturesque swimming bay offering 2 beach areas, both with lifeguards, showers & changing rooms.
detail_description: Clearwater Bay is a picturesque swimming destination with two beach areas, both equipped with lifeguards, showers, and changing rooms. Visitors can also enjoy dolphin tours from the marina area across the beach boardwalk. The bay offers breathtaking views of Clearwater's shores and crystal-clear waters. Boat tours are available for exploring the bay, offering glimpses of celebrity homes and plenty of dolphins. The area is rich in history and provides a beautiful setting for leisurely rides around the bay.
name: Clearwater Bay

detail_description: Coconut Kayak Tours offers a relaxing and enjoyable way to spend a day in Clearwater. The guide, KC, is highly praised for being wonderful, helpful, patient with kids, and knowledgeable about the area. Families have enjoyed kayaking adventures to beautiful spots like the 7 Sisters Springs and hidden mangrove canals around Caledesi Island. The tours are full of wildlife sightings and cool, clear waters.
name: Coconut Kayak Tours
address: Included Hotel Pick up & return van transportation. Max 6, persons, 69 Bay Esplanade, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: Aspirations Winery in Clearwater offers a delightful wine tasting experience with a great selection of wines to suit every palate. Located near Brighthouse Field, it's a popular spot for tours and tastings, as well as hosting events like bingo nights. Visitors have raved about the tour package, which includes trying five different wines of choice, receiving two stemless wine glasses, a free bottle of wine, and enjoying a tour of the facility accompanied by cheese, bread, grapes, and chocolate.
name: Aspirations Winery
address: 22041 US Hwy 19 N, Clearwater, FL 33765, USA

detail_description: The Clearwater Main Library is a spacious and modern space with a wide variety of books and activities for all ages. It's especially recommended for children due to its vast selection of books, activities, games, and dedicated areas for kids. The library also features a makerspace or medialab with access to computers equipped with great programs.
name: Clearwater Main Library
address: 100 N Osceola Ave, Clearwater, FL 33755, USA

excerpt: Beachfront green space with palm trees, multiple picnic pavilions & a playground.
detail_description: Nestled along the stunning Clearwater Beach, Pier 60 Park is a vibrant beachfront oasis that offers a delightful mix of relaxation and entertainment. This lush green space is adorned with swaying palm trees and features multiple picnic pavilions, making it an ideal spot for families to gather. Kids can enjoy the playground while adults take in the picturesque views or try their hand at fishing nearby. As day turns to night, Pier 60 Park transforms into a lively hub of activity with its famous Sunset Celebration.
name: Pier 60 Park
address: Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

detail_description: Clearwater offers a variety of boat tours for those looking to explore the waters. The Sea Screamer, known as the world's largest speed boat, provides an adrenaline-pumping experience with its twin-turbocharged engines and speeds of up to 35 miles per hour. Families can also opt for the pirate ship replica, Captain Memos Original Pirate Cruise, which offers interactive activities like treasure hunts and limbo dances.
name: Sea Screamer of Clearwater
address: 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Venue featuring lakeside trails, playgrounds, fishing & picnic areas, plus a 3-acre dog park.
detail_description: The Crest Lake Park is a great place to enjoy nature and relax. The park has several playgrounds, a large lake with fishing possibilities, a 3-acre dog park, and beautiful landscaping. The park also features trails that lead to the lakeside.
name: Crest Lake Park
address: 201 S Glenwood Ave, Clearwater, FL 33755, USA

excerpt: Heritage museum with exhibits on local pioneers & sports plus state citrus & railroad enterprises.
detail_description: The Dunedin History Museum, located at 349 Main Street, is a heritage museum that celebrates the legacy and heritage of Dunedin. It aims to enrich community pride by preserving historical artifacts and documents while fostering intergenerational learning through its exhibits.
name: Dunedin History Museum

detail_description: The Penny Lane Beatles Museum in Dunedin is a must-see for any Beatles enthusiast. This museum boasts an extensive collection of memorabilia and artifacts from the iconic band, offering a captivating glimpse into their history and enduring influence on music. Visitors can explore a treasure trove of Beatles-era items, including souvenirs, while being guided by knowledgeable curators who share fascinating stories and trivia about the Fab Four.
name: Penny Lane, Beatles Museum

excerpt: Lively boardwalk, popular for sunset views & fishing, with entertainers & artisanal craft stalls.
detail_description: Pier 60 in Clearwater is a vibrant boardwalk known for its stunning sunset views and fishing opportunities. Spanning just over 1,000 feet, it's a popular spot for artisans, street performers, and live entertainment. The pier hosts the nightly festival "Sunsets at Pier 60" and annual fireworks displays on Independence Day and New Year's Eve.
name: Pier 60 Clearwater
address: 1 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA
